{"title":"Kirshanthan (\"Krish\") Sundararajah","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Kirshanthan (\"Krish\") Sundararajah","about":{"template":"trestles","image":"images/avatar.jpg","image-shape":"rectangle","image-width":"200px","links":[{"icon":"envelope-fill","text":"Email","url":"mailto:kirshanthans@vt.edu"},{"icon":"mortarboard-fill","text":"Scholar","url":"https://scholar.google.com/citations?hl=en&user=knUrjrMAAAAJ&view_op=list_works&sortby=pubdate"},{"icon":"github","text":"GitHub","url":"https://github.com/kirshanthans"},{"icon":"twitter","text":"Twitter","url":"https://twitter.com/Kirshanthan"},{"icon":"linkedin","text":"LinkedIn","url":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/kirshanthan"},{"text":"**CV**","file":"files/cv/cv.pdf"}]}},"headingText":"Brief Bio","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n* **Position**: Assistant Professor\n* **Email**: [kirshanthans@vt.edu](mailto:kirshanthans@vt.edu)\n* **Affiliation**: [Virginia Tech](https://vt.edu) | [Computer Science](https://cs.vt.edu)\n* **Office**: GP 4103\n\nMy research interests span the areas of compilers, programming langauges and high-performance computing.\nI am particularly interested in solving performance and correctness challenges arise from the irregularity in computations.\n\nMy work spans following threads: control-flow regularization to improve performance and program analysis, building compiler infrastructure for sparse tensor computations, and developing principled approaches for transforming and optimizing recursive programs.\nSee my [Research](research.qmd) page for more.\n\nI received my PhD from [Purdue University](https://purdue.edu) where I was fortunate enough to advised by [Milind Kulkarni](https://engineering.purdue.edu/~milind).\nI was part of [PurPL](https://purduepl.github.io) at Purdue University.\nI earned my Bachelor's in Electronic and Telecommunication Engineering from [University of Moratuwa](https://uom.lk).\n"},"formats":{"html":{"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retin